cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with piano reduction, which involves converting an ensemble score into piano scores. This falls under the domain of sound and music processing.
- cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper presents an iterative optimization algorithm for piano reduction, which involves controlling the difficulty of the resulting piano scores. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses probabilistic generative models and statistical inference for developing performance difficulty measures and constructing a probabilistic model for musical fidelity. This falls under the domain of machine learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses computational methods for quantifying performance difficulty and optimizing musical fidelity, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a method for controlling performance difficulty in piano reduction, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
